---
/**
 * Validated holdout results — the instrument panel. Six readouts from the
 * first_attempt_v1 evaluation, stated plainly. The win rate is the only
 * number allowed a status color; abstention is slate, never red.
 */
---

<section class="proof section" id="proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Validated holdout · first_attempt_v1</p>
      <h2 class="title">Tested on jobs it had never seen.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Trained on 12,398 real production records, then evaluated on 2,043
        future holdout jobs. Color Brain never invents a recipe — it retrieves
        one your factory already ran, only on the same substrate, and only when
        confident.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="proof__grid reveal">
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value">12,398</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">production records trained on</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value">2,043</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">unseen holdout jobs tested</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value">414</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">jobs recommended — 20.3% coverage</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value proof__win">86.7%</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">win rate when it recommends</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value">+0.2082</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">median ΔE improvement on recommended jobs</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="proof__cell">
        <dt class="readout__value proof__abstain">~80%</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">abstention rate — calibrated silence, not failure</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <p class="proof__footnote reveal">
      On the ~80% of jobs where Color Brain abstains, it is saying the evidence
      isn't strong enough to beat your technician's first attempt. Selectivity
      is the point — a recommendation you can trust.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .proof {
    background: var(--bg);
    position: relative;
  }

  .proof__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    background: var(--line-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .proof__cell {
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
  }

  .proof__cell dd {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .proof__win {
    color: var(--win);
  }

  .proof__abstain {
    color: var(--abstain);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .proof__grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .proof__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .proof__footnote {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
</style>
